t", "The Nature Conservancy"], "highlights": "Stanford University is a world leader in environmental science research and education, with a strong focus on interdisciplinary approaches and innovative solutions. The university''s location in the heart of Silicon Valley provides unparalleled opportunities for collaboration and entrepreneurship. With a strong faculty and excellent resources, Stanford University is an ideal choice for students seeking a world-class education in environmental science.", "website": "https://www.stanford.edu/"}, {"name": "University of Oxford", "location": "Oxford, UK", "ranking": "#1 Globally", "admission_criteria": "Admission to the University of Oxford''s environmental science programs requires a strong academic record, with a minimum of A*A*A in A-levels. Students must also submit a personal statement and letters of recommendation, along with a non-refundable application fee of \u00a375. The application deadline is typically in October, with Oxbridge exams and interviews in December.", "courses_offered": ["B.A/M.A Environmental Studies", "M.Sc Environmental Change and Management", "D.Phil Environmental Research"], "placement_rate": "Near 100%", "avg_package": "\u00a330,000 - \u00a350,000 GBP", "top_recruiters": ["British Petroleum", "Royal Dutch Shell", "UK Government"], "highlights": "The University of Oxford is a world-renowned institution for environmental science research and education, with a strong focus on interdisciplinary approaches and cutting-edge research. The university''s academic programs are highly selective, with a strong emphasis on critical thinking and problem-solving. With a rich history and excellent resources, the University of Oxford is an ideal choice for students seeking a world-class education in environmental science.", "website": "https://www.ox.ac.uk/"}, {"name": "National University of Singapore (NUS)", "location": "Singapore", "ranking": "Top 2 in Asia", "admission_criteria": "Admission to NUS''s environmental science programs requires a strong academic record, with a minimum of 90% in the Indian 12th standard or equivalent. Students must also submit SAT or ACT scores, along with letters of recommendation and a personal statement. The application deadline is typically in February, with a non-refundable fee of SGD $20.", "courses_offered": ["B.Sc Environmental Biology", "M.Sc Environmental Science", "Ph.D Environmental Science"], "placement_rate": "95%", "avg_package": "SGD $50,000 - $70,000", "top_recruiters": ["Singapore Government", "Shell", "Procter & Gamble"], "highlights": "NUS is a world-class research university with a strong focus on environmental science and sustainability. The university''s academic programs are highly selective, with a strong emphasis on innovative research and problem-solving. With a rich cultural heritage and excellent resources, NUS is an ideal choice for students seeking a top-notch education in environmental science.", "website": "https://www.nus.edu.sg/"}, {"name": "Indian Institute of Science (IISc) Bangalore", "location": "Bangalore, India", "ranking": "Top 1 in India", "admission_criteria": "Admission to IISc''s environmental science programs is based on JAM scores, with a minimum cutoff of 35 for the general category. Eligible students must have completed 10+2 with a minimum of 60% marks in the science stream. The application process typically begins in February, with key dates including the JAM exam in February and the admission process in May.", "courses_offered": ["B.S Environmental Science", "M.Tech Environmental Engineering", "Ph.D Environmental Science"], "placement_rate": "95%", "avg_package": "8-10 lakhs INR", "top_recruiters": ["ISRO", "DRDO", "Indian Oil Corporation"], "highlights": "IISc is a premier research institution in India, with a strong focus on environmental science and sustainability. The institute''s academic programs are highly selective, with a strong emphasis on innovative research and problem-solving. With a rich heritage and excellent resources, IISc is an ideal choice for students seeking a world-class education in environmental science.", "website": "https://www.iisc.ac.in/"}], "preparation_tips": ["Develop a strong foundation in science and mathematics, particularly in subjects like biology, chemistry, and physics.", "Gain practical experience through internships, research projects, or volunteer work in environmental organizations to build a strong portfolio.", "Improve your critical thinking and problem-solving skills by participating in quizzes, competitions, and debates related to environmental science.", "Stay updated on current environmental issues and trends, and develop a clear understanding of the career paths and opportunities available in the field of environmental science."]}', '2026-04-08 06:30:46.820537+00'),
	(11, 7, 'Social Impact Consultant', '{"colleges": [{"name": "Indian Institute of Technology Delhi", "location": "New Delhi, India", "ranking": "Top 3 in India", "admission_criteria": "Admission to IIT Delhi is based on JEE Advanced exam scores, with a cutoff of 10,000 for the top 1000 ranks. Eligibility includes a minimum of 75% marks in the 12th standard. Key dates include May for JEE Advanced and June for counseling. Candidates must also meet the age criteria of being below 25 years.", "courses_offered": ["B.Tech Computer Science", "M.Tech Environmental Engineering", "M.Sc Economics"], "placement_rate": "95%", "avg_package": "15 lakhs INR", "top_recruiters": ["Google", "Microsoft", "Tata Consultancy Services"], "highlights": "IIT Delhi offers a unique blend of technical and social sciences courses, making it an ideal institution for students interested in social impact consulting. The institute has a strong focus on research and innovation, with numerous projects and collaborations with international organizations. Its location in the capital city provides access to a wide range of networking opportunities.", "website": "https://www.iitd.ac.in/"}, {"name": "University of California, Berkeley", "location": "Berkeley, USA", "ranking": "#12 Globally", "admission_criteria": "Admission to UC Berkeley requires SAT scores, with an average score of 1400, and a minimum GPA of 3.5. Eligibility includes completion of the A-G course requirements. Key dates include November for application submission and April for decision notification. International students must also submit TOEFL or IELTS scores.", "courses_offered": ["B.A. Environmental Economics", "M.S. Data Science", "M.P.P. Public Policy"], "placement_rate": "Near 100%", "avg_package": "80,000 USD", "top_recruiters": ["McKinsey", "Deloitte", "World Bank"], "highlights": "UC Berkeley is renowned for its strong programs in social sciences, environmental studies, and data science, making it an ideal destination for social impact consultants. The university has a diverse and vibrant community, with numerous opportunities for networking and collaboration. Its location in the San Francisco Bay Area provides access to a wide range of social impact organizations and startups.", "website": "https://www.berkeley.edu/"}, {"name": "Tata Institute of Social Sciences", "location": "Mumbai, India", "ranking": "Top 10 in India", "admission_criteria": "Admission to TISS is based on the TISSNET exam, with a cutoff of 60%. Eligibility includes a minimum of 50% marks in the 12th standard. Key dates include February for TISSNET and May for counseling. Candidates must also meet the age criteria of being below 28 years for some programs.", "courses_offered": ["M.A. Social Work", "M.Sc Development Studies", "M.A. Human Rights"], "placement_rate": "90%", "avg_package": "8 lakhs INR", "top_recruiters": ["Oxfam", "UNICEF", "ActionAid"], "highlights": "TISS is a premier institution for social sciences and social work, with a strong focus on social impact and community development. The institute has a wide range of programs and research centers, providing students with numerous opportunities for specialization and collaboration. Its location in Mumbai provides access to a diverse range of social impact organizations and NGOs.", "website": "https://www.tiss.edu/"}, {"name": "London School of Economics and Political Science", "location": "London, UK", "ranking": "#5 Globally", "admission_criteria": "Admission to LSE requires A-level grades, with a minimum of A*A*A, and a minimum GPA of 3.5. Eligibility includes completion of the A-level course requirements. Key dates include October for application submission and April for decision notification. International students must also submit IELTS scores.", "courses_offered": ["B.Sc Economics", "M.Sc Environmental Economics", "M.Sc Development Studies"], "placement_rate": "95%", "avg_package": "45,000 GBP", "top_recruiters": ["McKinsey", "Goldman Sachs", "World Bank"], "highlights": "LSE is a world-renowned institution for social sciences, economics, and politics, with a strong focus on research and policy analysis. The university has a diverse and international community, with numerous opportunities for networking and collaboration. Its location in London provides access to a wide range of social impact organizations, think tanks, and government institutions.", "website": "https://www.lse.ac.uk/"}, {"name": "Stanford University", "location": "Stanford, USA", "ranking": "#2 Globally", "admission_criteria": "Admission to Stanford requires SAT scores, with an average score of 1500, and a minimum GPA of 3.5. Eligibility includes completion of the A-G course requirements. Key dates include November for application submission and April for decision notification. International students must also submit TOEFL or IELTS scores.", "courses_offered": ["B.A. Economics", "M.S. Data Science", "M.A. Public Policy"], "placement_rate": "Near 100%", "avg_package": "100,000 USD", "top_recruiters": ["Google", "Facebook", "McKinsey"], "highlights": "Stanford is a world-leading institution for social sciences, economics, and data science, with a strong focus on innovation and entrepreneurship. The university has a diverse and vibrant community, with numerous opportunities for networking and collaboration. Its location in the Silicon Valley provides access to a wide range of social impact organizations, startups, and tech companies.", "website": "https://www.stanford.edu/"}], "preparation_tips": ["Develop a strong understanding of social sciences, economics, and data analysis, and stay updated on current global issues and trends.", "Gain practical experience through internships, volunteering, or research projects in social impact organizations, to build a strong portfolio and demonstrate commitment to the field.", "Improve language skills, particularly English, to meet the admission requirements of international universities and to enhance career opportunities.", "Prepare for standardized tests such as SAT, GRE, or GMAT, and practice with sample questions and mock tests to achieve a competitive score."]}', '2026-04-08 06:41:18.170222+00'),
	(12, 7, 'Human-Centered Design Specialist', '{"colleges": [{"name": "Indian Institute of Technology (IIT) Bombay", "location": "Mumbai, India", "ranking": "Top 3 in India", "admission_criteria": "Admission is based on JEE Advanced scores, with a typical cutoff of 2000-3000 for the design program. Eligible candidates must have passed 10+2 with a minimum of 75% marks. Key dates include the JEE Advanced exam in May and counseling in June-July.", "courses_offered": ["B.Des Industrial Design", "M.Des Industrial Design", "Ph.D. Design"], "placement_rate": "95%", "avg_package": "15-20 lakhs INR", "top_recruiters": ["Tata Consulting Engineers", "Godrej", "Whirlpool"], "highlights": "IIT Bombay''s design program is highly regarded for its emphasis on human-centered design, with a strong focus on user research and innovation. The institute''s research centers and incubators provide students with opportunities to work on real-world projects. The program''s interdisciplinary approach prepares students for a wide range of design careers.", "website": "https://www.iitb.ac.in/"}, {"name": "Carnegie Mellon University", "location": "Pittsburgh, USA", "ranking": "#12 Globally", "admission_criteria": "Admission requires SAT or ACT scores, with a typical range of 1450-1550 for design programs. Eligible candidates must have passed 10+2 with a minimum GPA of 3.5. Key dates include the application deadline in January and decision notification in April.", "courses_offered": ["BFA Design", "M.Des", "M.Sc Human-Computer Interaction"], "placement_rate": "Near 100%", "avg_package": "80,000-100,000 USD", "top_recruiters": ["Google", "Microsoft", "Adobe"], "highlights": "Carnegie Mellon''s School of Design is renowned for its human-centered design approach, with a strong focus on user experience and social impact. The program''s interdisciplinary nature allows students to collaborate with peers from other departments, such as computer science and engineering. The university''s location in Pittsburgh provides access to a thriving design community.", "website": "https://www.cmu.edu/"}, {"name": "National Institute of Design (NID) Ahmedabad", "location": "Ahmedabad, India", "ranking": "Top 1 in India for Design", "admission_criteria": "Admission is based on the NID DAT exam, with a typical cutoff of 50-60. Eligible candidates must have passed 10+2 with a minimum of 50% marks. Key dates include the DAT exam in January and counseling in April-May.", "courses_offered": ["B.Des Product Design", "M.Des Product Design", "PGDPD"], "placement_rate": "90%", "avg_package": "10-15 lakhs INR", "top_recruiters": ["L&T", "Mahindra", "Tata Motors"], "highlights": "NID Ahmedabad is India''s premier design institute, with a strong focus on human-centered design and sustainability. The program''s emphasis on hands-on learning and industry partnerships provides students with practical experience and networking opportunities. The institute''s campus is a design hub, with a vibrant community of designers and entrepreneurs.", "website": "https://www.nid.edu/"}, {"name": "Royal College of Art (RCA)", "location": "London, UK", "ranking": "#1 in the World for Art and Design", "admission_criteria": "Admission requires a strong portfolio and academic record, with a typical GPA of 3.5 or higher. Eligible candidates must have passed 10+2 with a minimum of 50% marks. Key dates include the application deadline in January and decision notification in April.", "courses_offered": ["MA Design Interactions", "MA Service Design", "MPhil/Ph.D. Design"], "placement_rate": "95%", "avg_package": "40,000-60,000 GBP", "top_recruiters": ["Apple", "BMW", "IBM"], "highlights": "The RCA is a global leader in art and design education, with a strong focus on human-centered design and innovation. The program''s interdisciplinary approach allows students to collaborate with peers from other departments, such as engineering and business. The college''s location in London provides access to a thriving design scene and industry networks.", "website": "https://www.rca.ac.uk/"}, {"name": "Symbiosis Institute of Design (SID)", "location": "Pune, India", "ranking": "Top 10 in India for Design", "admission_criteria": "Admission is based on the SEED exam, with a typical cutoff of 50-60. Eligible candidates must have passed 10+2 with a minimum of 50% marks. Key dates include the SEED exam in May and counseling in June-July.", "courses_offered": ["B.Des Product Design", "B.Des Communication Design", "M.Des"], "placement_rate": "85%", "avg_package": "8-12 lakhs INR", "top_recruiters": ["Wipro", "HCL", "Oracle"], "highlights": "SID is a leading design institute in India, with a strong focus on human-centered design and industry partnerships. The program''s emphasis on hands-on learning and project-based learning provides students with practical experience and networking opportunities. The institute''s location in Pune provides access to a thriving design community and industry networks.", "website": "https://sid.siu.edu.in/"}], "preparation_tips": ["Develop a strong portfolio showcasing your design skills and projects, with a focus on human-centered design principles and user research.", "Prepare for design entrance exams like NID DAT, SEED, or JEE Advanced, and practice with sample questions and mock tests.", "Build a strong foundation in design fundamentals, including visual design, user experience, and design thinking, through online courses or workshops.", "Network with design professionals and attend design events to learn about industry trends and best practices, and to build connections in the design community."]}', '2026-04-08 06:47:15.767952+00'),
	(13, 19, 'Software Engineering with a specialization in User Experience (UX) Design', '{"colleges": [{"name": "Vellore Institute of Technology", "location": "Vellore, India", "ranking": "Top Private College in South India", "admission_criteria": "VIT accepts scores from VITEEE, JEE Main, and SAT. Eligibility includes a minimum of 60% in 12th standard with PCM. Approximate cutoffs for VITEEE range from 1000 to 5000. The admission process involves online registration, exam, and counseling.", "courses_offered": ["B.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering", "B.Tech in Information Technology", "M.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering with specialization in UX"], "placement_rate": "80-90%", "avg_package": "6-10 LPA", "top_recruiters": ["TCS", "Infosys", "Wipro"], "highlights": "VIT is a good fit for this student due to its emphasis on practical learning, collaborative campus culture, and strong industry connections. The adaptive explorer archetype will benefit from VIT''s diverse range of courses and electives, while the ambivert personality will appreciate the balance between academic and extracurricular activities.", "website": "https://vit.ac.in/"}, {"name": "SRM Institute of Science and Technology", "location": "Chennai, India", "ranking": "Top Private University in Tamil Nadu", "admission_criteria": "SRM accepts scores from SRMJEEE, JEE Main, and NEET. Eligibility includes a minimum of 60% in 12th standard with PCM. Approximate cutoffs for SRMJEEE range from 5000 to 20000. The admission process involves online registration, exam, and counseling.", "courses_offered": ["B.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering", "B.Tech in Software Engineering", "M.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering with specialization in UX"], "placement_rate": "85-95%", "avg_package": "7-12 LPA", "top_recruiters": ["Amazon", "Microsoft", "Google"], "highlights": "SRM is a good fit for this student due to its strong focus on research and development, innovative campus culture, and excellent placement records. The adaptive explorer archetype will benefit from SRM''s interdisciplinary courses and projects, while the ambivert personality will appreciate the opportunities for leadership and teamwork.", "website": "https://www.srmist.edu.in/"}, {"name": "Manipal Institute of Technology", "location": "Manipal, India", "ranking": "Top Private College in Karnataka", "admission_criteria": "MIT accepts scores from MET, JEE Main, and UGET. Eligibility includes a minimum of 60% in 12th standard with PCM. Approximate cutoffs for MET range from 1000 to 5000. The admission process involves online registration, exam, and counseling.", "courses_offered": ["B.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering", "B.Tech in Information Technology", "M.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering with specialization in UX"], "placement_rate": "80-90%", "avg_package": "6-11 LPA", "top_recruiters": ["TCS", "Infosys", "Wipro"], "highlights": "MIT is a good fit for this student due to its emphasis on hands-on learning, collaborative campus culture, and strong industry connections. The adaptive explorer archetype will benefit from MIT''s flexible curriculum and interdisciplinary courses, while the ambivert personality will appreciate the opportunities for extracurricular activities and community engagement.", "website": "https://manipal.edu/mu.html"}, {"name": "Thapar Institute of Engineering and Technology", "location": "Patiala, India", "ranking": "Top Private College in North India", "admission_criteria": "TIET accepts scores from JEE Main, NEET, and 12th standard marks. Eligibility includes a minimum of 60% in 12th standard with PCM. Approximate cutoffs for JEE Main range from 10000 to 50000. The admission process involves online registration and counseling.", "courses_offered": ["B.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering", "B.Tech in Information Technology", "M.Tech in Computer Science and Engineering with specialization in UX"], "placement_rate": "85-95%", "avg_package": "7-12 LPA", "top_recruiters": ["Amazon", "Microsoft", "Google"], "highlights": "TIET is a good fit for this student due to its strong focus on academic excellence, research-oriented campus culture, and excellent placement records. The adaptive explorer archetype will benefit from TIET''s rigorous curriculum and faculty mentorship, while the ambivert personality will appreciate the opportunities for leadership and teamwork.", "website": "https://thapar.edu/"}, {"name": "Birla Institute of Technology and Science", "location": "Pilani, India", "ranking": "Top Private University in Rajasthan", "admission_criteria": "BITS accepts scores from BITSAT, JEE Main, and 12th standard marks. Eligibility includes a minimum of 60% in 12th standard with PCM. Approximate cutoffs for BITSAT range from 200 to 300. The admission process involves online registration, exam, and counseling.", "courses_offered": ["B.E. in Computer Science", "B.E. in Information Technology", "M.E. in Computer Science with specialization in UX"], "placement_rate": "85-95%", "avg_package": "8-14 LPA", "top_recruiters": ["Amazon", "Microsoft", "Google"], "highlights": "BITS is a good fit for this student due to its emphasis on interdisciplinary learning, innovative campus culture, and strong industry connections. The adaptive explorer archetype will benefit from BITS'' flexible curriculum and research opportunities, while the ambivert personality will appreciate the opportunities for extracurricular activities and community engagement.", "website": "https://www.bits-pilani.ac.in/"}], "preparation_tips": ["Focus on developing a strong foundation in programming languages, data structures, and algorithms to prepare for entrance exams and campus placements.", "Participate in hackathons, coding challenges, and online communities to improve coding skills and build a portfolio of projects.", "Develop a good understanding of UX design principles, human-computer interaction, and user-centered design methodologies to enhance career prospects in UX design.", "Build a strong online presence, including a LinkedIn profile and personal website or blog, to showcase skills, projects, and experiences to potential recruiters."]}', '2026-04-14 10:16:57.195981+00');


